## GITOPS R2 database backup rollout (2026-07-14)

- Implemented and deployed the governed `CloudMCP -> GitOps -> Cloudapi assets -> R2` logical-backup path, 30-day retention cleanup, checksum manifest, distinct-target restore contract, and Cloudapi asset deletion; no direct R2/S3 credentials or endpoint were added.
- Production acceptance on `db-jw-primary` proved synchronous requests hit Cloudflare 524, so backup execution was converted to managed asynchronous Agent jobs with polling, lost-job reconciliation, 20-minute process-group termination, and 1 MiB Cloudapi chunks.
- Superseded by production acceptance: `backup-db-jw-primary-1784025760330` reached `status=success` with SHA, size, two parts, expiry, and `cloudapi_read_verified=true`. Backup governance is now deployed with pool defaults, cluster inherit/override, manual backup, asynchronous restore, status/error evidence, and retryable 30-day cleanup.
- GitOps `0d9d47f` and CloudMCP `5ad275f` are deployed and their test/deploy gates passed. Production browser automation reached the expected Cloudflare Access login boundary; authenticated visual inspection was not possible without a user session, while final HTML/script behavior remains covered by the UI regression suite.
- 2026-07-14 load-governance follow-up is complete: GitOps `9de3072` adds deterministic four-hour staggering, D1 atomic global 2 / per-Agent 1 leases, queued admission for manual and scheduled requests, stale-start recovery, and five-attempt Cloudapi upload backoff. Cloudapi `f35a78e` adds project-scoped idempotent private asset creation; `96eb49e` leaves CodeQL analysis enabled while disabling unsupported SARIF upload. Four simultaneous production acceptance backups proved 2/1 limits, queue handoff, final success, and R2 read verification. All relevant GitHub workflows are green.
